## Additional Risks
- The prompt mixes UX instructions, implementation details, and API assumptions in the same step. That makes it harder for an implementer to tell which parts are non-negotiable and which are examples.
- The save-flow ambiguity is the highest practical risk: it can produce code that appears to work in one UI path but bypasses existing invariants or toast behavior in another.
